(17) One member to represent the League of Women Voters, appointed by the league.
(18) One member to represent the La. Press Assoc. and one member to represent the La.
Assoc. of Broadcasters, appoint by the president of each association.
(19) One member to represent the La. Center for Law and Civic Education, appointed by
the president of its board of directors.
(20) One member to represent the La. Assoc. of Non-Profit Organizations, appointed by
the chairman of the association.
(21) One member to represent the La. Chapter of the National Assoc. for the
Advancement of Colored People, appointed by the president of the chapter.
(22) The chairman of the Volunteer La. Commission, or his designee.
(23) Any additional member who has expertise in civic education or civic involvement,
as may be designated by 3/4 of the commission members present and voting. Such
member shall serve at the pleasure of the commission.
(24) One member from the La. District Judges Assoc. who shall be appointed by the
president of its board of directors to the commission.
(25) The chief justice of the La. Supreme Court, or his designee.
Proposed law retains present law and adds the president of the Power Coalition for Equity
and Justice or his designee to the commission.
Effective upon signature of governor or lapse of time for gubernatorial action.
